'''Gilberto Rafael Mora Zambrano''' (born 14 October 2008) is a Mexican professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Liga MX]] club [[Club Tijuana|Tijuana]] and the [[Mexico national football team|Mexico national team]].

==Early life==
Mora was born on 14 October 2008 in [[Tuxtla Gutiérrez]], Mexico. He is the son of former footballer [[Gilberto Mora (footballer, born 1976)|Gilberto Mora]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sopitas.com/deportes/quien-es-gilberto-mora-hijo-exfutbolista-goleador-mas-joven-liga-mx-barcelona/|title=¿Quién es Gilberto Mora, hijo de exfutbolista y goleador más joven de la Liga MX?|date=17 September 2024 |publisher=sopitas.com}}</ref>

==Club career==
Mora joined the youth academy of [[Club Tijuana]], and was described as "one of the most outstanding players in the lower divisions of the team".<ref name="Mora1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.futboltotal.com.mx/futbol-mexicano/liga-mx/quien-es-gilberto-mora-joya-de-los-xolos-de-tijuana/2024/08/|title=¿Quién es Gilberto Mora? Joya de los Xolos de Tijuana|date=19 August 2024|publisher=futboltotal.com.mx}}</ref> After just a few weeks of training with the first-team, head coach [[Juan Carlos Osorio]] included Mora in the squad for the [[2024–25 Liga MX season|2024–25 season]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Él es Gilberto Mora, el "niño" de 15 años que debutó con Xolos con todo y una asistencia|url=https://soyreferee.com/tendencias/2024/8/18/quien-es-gilberto-mora-15-anos-debut-xolos-tijuana-liga-mx-29296.html|date=18 August 2024|access-date=7 July 2025|archive-date=14 October 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241014205455/https://soyreferee.com/tendencias/2024/8/18/quien-es-gilberto-mora-15-anos-debut-xolos-tijuana-liga-mx-29296.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 19 August 2024, he made his [[Liga MX]] debut against [[Santos Laguna]], replacing [[Efraín Álvarez]] in the 72nd minute and provided the assist for Jaime Álvarez's goal in Tijuana's 3–1 victory. At 15 years, ten months and five days old, Mora became Tijuana's youngest-ever debutant, the third-youngest player to debut in Liga MX, and the youngest player to provide an assist.<ref name="Mora1" /> On 31 August, Mora scored his first goal in Tijuana's 2–1 win over [[Club León|León]], becoming the youngest player to score in the Mexican top flight at 15 years and 320 days old.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.milenio.com/futbol/liga-mx/quien-es-gilberto-mora-goleador-mas-joven-en-la-historia-liga-mx|title=¿Quién es Gilberto Mora, el jugador más joven en anotar en la historia de la Liga MX?|date=31 August 2024 |work=[[Milenio]]}}</ref>

On 31 July 2025, Mora scored his first brace in Tijuana's 5–2 [[2025 Leagues Cup|Leagues Cup]] defeat against [[LA Galaxy]]. On 16 August, returning to Liga MX, Mora scored in his team's 2–0 victory against [[C.F. Pachuca|Pachuca]]. On 22 August, Mora scored another brace, this time in a 3–3 draw against [[C.D. Guadalajara|Guadalajara]].

==International career==
As a youth international, Mora has played for Mexico's [[Mexico national under-15 football team|under-15]], under-16, and [[Mexico national under-17 football team|under-17 team]]s. He made sixteen appearances and scored nine goals while playing for the under-15 side, and captained the under-17 team as a 15-year old.

On 16 January 2025, Mora made his debut with the [[Mexico national football team|senior side]] in an unofficial friendly against [[SC Internacional]] a team from [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]], making him the youngest player to appear for the national team at 16 years old.<ref>{{cite web|title=This Wonderkid Could Play in Three World Cups in Nine Months - and He's on Chelsea and Man United's Radar|url=https://footballpark.com/football-blogs/the-16-year-old-wonderkid-who-could-play-in-three-world-cups-in-nine-months-and-he-s-on-chelsea-and-man-united-s-radar|publisher=Football Park|date=8 October 2025|access-date=10 October 2025}}</ref>

Mora was included in the provisional 60-man list for the [[2025 CONCACAF Nations League Finals]], and made the 26-man squad for the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]]. On 28 June, he received a starting berth in the quarter-final match against [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]], thereby officially becoming the youngest-ever player to debut for Mexico.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|title=Gilberto Mora, oficialmente el jugador más jóven en debutar con México|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/selecciones/nota/_/id/15367213/gilberto-mora-mexico-debut-mas-joven-partido-oficial-copa-oro|publisher=ESPN Deportes|language=Spanish|access-date=28 June 2025}}</ref> In the semi-final, Mora provided his first assist in the 1–0 victory over [[Honduras national football team|Honduras]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-02 |title=Mexico vs Honduras live score, H2H and lineups {{!}} Sofascore |url=https://www.sofascore.com/en-us/football/match/wqf3-concacaf-wqf2-concacaf/GVbsCWb#id:14000198 |access-date=2025-07-06}}</ref> He then started in the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup final|final]] against the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]], where Mexico would win their 10th title. Later that year, he was called up by coach [[Eduardo Arce]] to represent Mexico at the [[2025 FIFA U-20 World Cup|FIFA U-20 World Cup]] held in Chile.<ref>{{cite web|title=Convocatoria Oficial de México Sub-20 para el Mundial de Chile|url=https://miseleccion.mx/noticias/6147/Convocatoria-Oficial-de-M%C3%A9xico-Sub-20-para-el-Mundial-de-Chile|website=MiSeleccion.mx|date=10 September 2025|access-date=27 September 2025|language=Spanish}}</ref>

On May 31, 2026, Mora was called up for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup]], becoming the tournament’s youngest player.<ref>{{Cite web |title=World Cup's youngest player, Mexico's Gilberto Mora, 26 years younger than the oldest |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/48955103/mexico-gilberto-mora-17-youngest-player-world-cup |access-date=2026-06-04 |website=ESPN}}</ref>

